<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_iblis" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>iblis</orth><form type="variant"><orth>ibiliz</orth></form></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>дьявол</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>devil</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>демон</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>demon</q></cit></sense></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_iblis." n=""><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>ibiliztæ, ʒintæ, æ sajtani xæjttæ…</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>иблисы, джины, его шайтановы доли…</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>iblises, djinns, his Satanic henchmen</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>21</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>ibiliztæ, ʒintæ, æ sajtani xæjttæ…</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>иблисы, джины, его шайтановы доли…</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>iblises, djinns, his Satanic henchmen</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>21</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/><w>iblīs</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>iblīs</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>iblis</w><gloss><q>дьявол</q></gloss></mentioned>. Вошло и в другие языки Кавказа: <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>’iblis</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>ilbis, iblis</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/><w>iblis</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/><w>jilbaz, lilbaz</w></mentioned> и др. Ос. <xr><ref target="#entry_fydbylyz"/></xr> ‘беда’ (см. это слово) образовалось из <xr><ref target="#entry_fyd"/></xr>-%iiblis%i ‘злой демон’.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/><w>iblīs</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>iblīs</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>iblis</w><gloss><q>devil</q></gloss></mentioned>. Iy entered other languages of Caucasus as well: <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>’iblis</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>ilbis, iblis</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/><w>iblis</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/><w>jilbaz, lilbaz</w></mentioned> etc. Ossetic <xr><ref target="#entry_fydbylyz"/></xr> ‘misfortune’ (see this word) was formed from <xr><ref target="#entry_fyd"/></xr>-%iiblis%i ‘evil demon’.</etym><note type="internal">перевод примера!!</note></entry>